        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 5:56PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 555 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Fort Benton, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Benton, Geraldine, and Square Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
north central Montana.</instruction>
